<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst-pr" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">SWR Observations</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">SWR Observations</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWR Observations</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Data_Visualization_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Data Visualization</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. It is used to display data generated by SWR Observations along a series of reaches defined by the selected objects. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Data_Visualization_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Data Visualization</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is first displayed, the selected objects are used to determine which SWR reaches to plot. To change the reaches to plot, click the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Get selected reaches</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button. Before data can be plotted, you must first define SWR Observations. SWR Observations can be defined either for </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Reaches_in_SWR_Surface_Water_R" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">specific objects</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SWR_Observations_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">SWR Observations</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box. You must then run MODFLOW and select the file containing the observation results. If any of the reaches contain observations of the selected type, The will be plotted in a graph for the selected time. ModelMuse will attempt to arrange the reaches using the connections between reaches. Lines will be drawn between successive points in the graph if the reaches for those points are connected.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The plots can be animated by clicking the Animate button. The animation interval is the time in seconds between when one plot in the animation series is displayed and when the next is displayed.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Because no data from the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWR Observations</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is saved, the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Apply</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button is disabled when the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">SWR Observations</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is being used.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
